<TITLE> PM to open employment programme in Kurigram Saturday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kurigram, Mar 5 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina will be visiting Kurigram on Saturday to inaugurate the government's country-wide employment generation programme 'National Service'. The district town has been adorned with banners, posters and festoons as part of the festivities to greet the prime minister. The stage for the inauguration has been made in the shape of a large boat. Acting deputy commissioner of the district, Faruk Hossain said, "The prime minister will inaugurate the 'National Service', an employment generation programme that includes professional and creative training for youth aged 18-35 years with higher secondary or equivalent educational qualification." "Under the programme, employment opportunities will be opened to 32,554 youths of Kurigram district. Of them, 9,950 will be employed within the current fiscal year." They will be trained for three months in 10 different areas, namely  disaster management and social service, computer education, self-employment, different service-oriented fields, education and physical education, agriculture, forestry and environment, public security and law and order." Water resources minister Ramesh Chandra Sen, state minister for land Mustafizur Rahman, youth and sports state minister Ahad Ali Sarker, state minister for primary education Mohammad Motahar are expected to be p
